Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop
the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Zest and halve the
@lemon{1/2}(zested and halved).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, lemon zest,
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} for the marinade, half the garlic
and three quarters of the @peri peri seasoning{2}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, mix together, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat (If you
don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal #saucepan{} and transfer to an
ovenproof dish later).

Once hot, add the onion and season with salt and pepper. Stir-fry until soft
and golden, ~{6-8%mins}.

Meanwhile, soak your @bamboo skewers{4} in cold water to prevent them from
burning.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{3} into 2cm chunks and add them to the marinade
bowl. Mix well to coat, then set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the onion has softened, stir in the remaining garlic and cook for
~{1%min}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges are
translucent, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @water{450%ml} for the rice, @chicken stock paste{20%g} and
remaining peri peri. Bring to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover
with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is
cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%mins}.

Meanwhile, thread the chicken pieces onto the skewers (2 per person) and
transfer to a #baking tray{}.

Once the rice has baked for 10 mins, bake the skewers on the top shelf of
your oven until cooked through, ~{10-15%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the rice is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @butter{30%g},
@peas{120%g}, a squeeze of lemon juice and two thirds of the parsley.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed. Add a splash
of water if it's a little thick.

Spoon the rice into your #bowls{} and serve the chicken skewers on top.
Sprinkle over the remaining parsley to finish.

Enjoy!